Interface Queue<E>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<E>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ByteQueue, CircularQueue, UnboundQueue

    public interface Queue<E>
extends java.lang.Iterable<E>

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      boolean empty()
      Returns true if this queue contains no elements.
      boolean full()
      Returns true if no space is currently available in this queue (cannot put more elements).
      E get()
      Retrieves and removes the head of this queue, or throws an exception if this queue is empty.
      boolean hasFree(int n)
      Returns true if the space currently available in this queue is greater or equal than the given value.
      E peekFirst()
      Retrieves, but does not remove, the head (first element) of this queue, or returns null if this queue is empty.
      E peekLast()
      Retrieves, but does not remove, the tail (last element) of this queue, or returns null if this queue is empty.
      void put(E e)
      Inserts the specified element at the tail of this queue, or throws an exception if this queue is full.
      int size()
      Returns the number of elements in this queue
